ound speed, GPS coordinates, pitch, roll, heading, throttle, battery, and m=
otor status, plus an arm/disarm switch and keyboard controls for moving up,=
 down, left, and right. Working with the simulator helped me practice keepi=
ng the drone steady, reading instruments, and understanding how small input=
s change the flight =E2=80=94 without the risk of crashing real hardware.</=
p><div class=3D"tech-tags"><span>Drone Flight</span><span>Simulation</span>=
